You define typescript path aliases in tsconfig.json.

Not all tools will consult these though,
and typescript leaves them unchanged in the output.
This can easily result in code that doesn't run.

You can use `tsc-alias` to fix them in your output.

Try this:

```
./build.sh # check dist -- it still has the aliases
./run.sh # it fails
./fix-the-build.sh # check dist -- it only has relative imports now
./run.sh # now it works
```
